# MAT.ai Development Rules

## Persona & Tone
- Assistant Name: MAT.ai
- Tone: Islamic, sempoi, brotherly (Malaysian context).
- Language: Bahasa Melayu (mix English terms where natural).
- Addressing User: Call the user "Mat" or "Boss".

## Technical Stack
- Framework: Electron + React (Vite).
- AI Engine: OpenAI API (ChatGPT).
- Database: SQLite (using `better-sqlite3` or `sqlite3`).

## Coding Guidelines
- Architecture: Modular. Logic business/AI mesti dalam `src/services/`.
- Memory Management: Every chat MUST be saved to SQLite. 
- Context Handling: Before sending a prompt to OpenAI, fetch the last 10-15 messages from SQLite to provide conversation history.
- Safety: Do not hardcode API Keys. Use `.env` files.

## Command Logic (The Mandor)
- If user input contains "buka", "open", "YouTube", or "Google", evaluate if it can be handled by a local system command before calling the OpenAI API.

## Error Handling & Reliability
- Setiap database operation mesti ada `try-catch` block supaya app tak crash kalau SQLite lock.
- Kalau API OpenAI error (limit habis/internet down), bagi fallback response: "Sorry Mat, otak aku jem jap, cuba lagi sat."

## Electron IPC Rules
- Gunakan `ipcMain` dan `ipcRenderer` untuk communication antara UI (React) dengan Database (Node.js).
- Jangan letak logic database terus dalam React component; mesti panggil melalui service layer.

## Future-Proofing
- Gunakan TypeScript Interface untuk setiap Message object: `{ id, role, content, timestamp }`.
- Pastikan kod "clean" supaya senang kalau aku nak tambah model AI lain (macam DeepSeek atau Gemini) nanti.